  "prompt": "What step must taken to make Indian Politics more transparent? Corruption free?",
  "response": "To make Indian politics more transparent and corruption-free, several key steps can be taken:\n\n1. Electoral Reforms\n- Stricter campaign finance regulations\n- Transparent funding of political parties\n- Electoral bonds accountability\n- Comprehensive income disclosure by candidates\n\n2. Strong Anti-Corruption Mechanisms\n- Strengthen Lokpal and Lokayukta institutions\n- Empower investigative agencies\n- Fast-track corruption cases\n- Robust whistleblower protection\n\n3. Technology and Digital Transparency\n- Online RTI platforms\n- Digital tracking of government expenditures\n- Blockchain-based voting systems\n- Mandatory digital financial disclosures\n\n4. Judicial Reforms\n- Speedy trial of corruption cases\n- Independent judiciary\n- Stringent punishment for corrupt practices\n- Judicial accountability\n\n5. Internal Party Democracy\n- Transparent candidate selection processes\n- Regular internal elections\n- Merit-based leadership selection\n- Reduce dynastic politics\n\n6. Citizen Participation\n- Enhanced civic education\n- Active public monitoring\n- Encouraging youth participation\n- Strong media oversight\n\n7. Administrative Reforms\n- Merit-based bureaucratic appointments\n- Simplified government procedures\n- Reducing discretionary powers\n- Performance-based evaluations\n\n8. Legal Framework\n- Comprehensive anti-corruption legislation\n- Strict implementation of existing laws\n- Removing legal loopholes\n- Proportionate punishments\n\nImplementing these steps systematically can significantly improve political transparency and reduce corruption.",
